\begin{pro}\label{reduction}
Let $n \geq 2$. Assume $n$ is odd (resp. even). The simplicial complex ${\Delta(n)}$ is CM if and only if $\widetilde{H_i}({\Delta}(l); {\mathbb K})=0$ for every $l\leq n$, with $l$ odd (resp. even), and for every $i<\dim({\Delta}(l))$.
