Putting together the results of the previous sections we obtain the following classification of $T_n$ in terms
of the CM property:

\begin{teo}\label{main}
For triangular graphs $T_n$, the following holds:
\begin{itemize}
\item[(i)] $T_2$, $T_3$ and $T_5$ are CM graphs. 
\item[(ii)] $T_7$ and $T_9$ are CM graphs over any field of characteristic zero.
